ing in 1611, since \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]creature\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] could mean simply \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]created thing\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and could function more broadly than it usually does today; modern English tends to hear \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]creature\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] zoologically or individually. \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Manifestation\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] for \:1f00\[Pi]\[Omicron]\[Kappa]\:03ac\[Lambda]\[Upsilon]\[Psi]\[Iota]\[Nu] is defensible but slightly less apocalyptic than \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]revelation/unveiling.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] Also \:1f00\[Pi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Kappa]\[Delta]\:03ad\[Chi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Tau]\[Alpha]\[Iota] is deponent/middle in form and already means \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]wait eagerly,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] so KJV distributes the eagerness into \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]earnest expectation,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] while the modern keeps it in \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]eager longing.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]\"\n}"|>, <|"ref" -> "Ro 8:5", "greek" -> "\[Omicron]\:1f31 \[Gamma]\:1f70\[Rho] \[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\:1f70 \[Sigma]\:03ac\[Rho]\[Kappa]\[Alpha] \:1f44\[Nu]\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[FinalSigma] \[Tau]\:1f70 \[Tau]\:1fc6\[FinalSigma] \[Sigma]\[Alpha]\[Rho]\[Kappa]\:1f78\[FinalSigma] \[CurlyPhi]\[Rho]\[Omicron]\[Nu]\[Omicron]\:1fe6\[Sigma]\[Iota]\[Nu], \[Omicron]\:1f31 \[Delta]\:1f72 \[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\:1f70 \[Pi]\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fe6\[Mu]\[Alpha] \[Tau]\:1f70 \[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 \[Pi]\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:03cd\[Mu]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma].", "kjv" -> "For they that are after the flesh do mind the things of the flesh; but they that are after the Spirit the things of the Spirit.", "modern" -> "For those who are according to the flesh set their minds on the things of the flesh, but those who are according to the Spirit on the things of the Spirit.", "distance" -> 0.17695177652038585, "nuance" -> <|"primary_nuance" -> "The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]do mind\[CloseC