 is also slightly compressed in the KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s cleft, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]It is God that justifieth\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; the modern \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]God is the one who justifies\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] more visibly mirrors \:1f41 \[Delta]\[Iota]\[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[Iota]\:1ff6\[Nu]. The forensic pairing with \[Tau]\:03af\[FinalSigma] \:1f41 \[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\[Alpha]\[Kappa]\[Rho]\[Iota]\[Nu]\:1ff6\[Nu] in v. 34 confirms that Paul is thinking in courtroom terms: accusation is futile because the judge is the justifying God.\"\n}"|>, <|"ref" -> "Ro 8:9", "greek" -> "\:1f59\[Mu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fd6\[FinalSigma] \[Delta]\:1f72 \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f10\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:1f72 \:1f10\[Nu] \[Sigma]\[Alpha]\[Rho]\[Kappa]\:1f76 \:1f00\[Lambda]\[Lambda]\:1f70 \:1f10\[Nu] \[Pi]\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:03cd\[Mu]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\[Iota], \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f34\[Pi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Rho] \[Pi]\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fe6\[Mu]\[Alpha] \[Theta]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 \[Omicron]\:1f30\[Kappa]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fd6 \:1f10\[Nu] \:1f51\[Mu]\:1fd6\[Nu]. \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f30 \[Delta]\:03ad \[Tau]\[Iota]\[FinalSigma] \[Pi]\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fe6\[Mu]\[Alpha] \[CapitalChi]\[Rho]\[Iota]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f14\[Chi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Iota], \[Omicron]\:1f57\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f14\[Sigma]\[Tau]\[Iota]\[Nu] \[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6.", "kjv" -> "But ye are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if so be that the Spirit of God dwell in you. Now if any man have not the Spirit of Christ, he is none of his.", "modern" -> "You, however, are not in the flesh but in the Spirit, if indeed the Spirit of God dwells in you. But if anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, this person does not belong to him.", "distance" -> 0.16262731193596125, "nuance" -> <|"primary_nuance" -> "The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]he is none of his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is an older possessive idiom meaning \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]does not belong to him,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] while the Greek \[Omicron]\:1f57\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f14\[Sigma]\[Tau]\[Iota]\[Nu] \[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 states non-belonging to Christ rather than a vague loss of identity.", "category" -> "archaic-english-drift", "key_term" -> "\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f30\[Mu]\:03af", "english_drift" -> "\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]none of his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] = in early modern English, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]not one belonging to him / not his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; in modern English it can sound opaque or merely idiomatic rather than explicitly possessive.", "textual_note" -> "", "cross_refs" -> {"1 Cor 3:16", "Gal 4:6", "Rom 8:14"}, "explanation" -> "There is no meaningful TR/SBLGNT divergence here; the issue is chiefly idiom and aspect. \[Omicron]\:1f57\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f14\[Sigma]\[Tau]\[Iota]\[Nu] \[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 is a genitive of possession or relationship: \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]this one is not his,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] i.e. does not belong to Christ. The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]he is none of his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] was intelligible early modern English, but now risks opacity; the modern rendering makes the possessive force explicit. Likewise \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]if so be that\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] renders \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f34\[Pi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Rho], which BDAG treats as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]if indeed / if in fact\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; with the indicative \[Omicron]\:1f30\[Kappa]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fd6 it is not a subjunctive \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]might dwell,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] but a condition assumed for Paul\[CloseCurlyQuote]s addressees. The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s bare \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]dwell\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] also reflects older English verbal usage, whereas \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]dwells\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] marks the present indicative more transparently. The alternation \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Spirit of God\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] / \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Spirit of Christ\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is in the Greek and is theologically significant, but not a KJV addition."|>, "raw" -> "{\n  \"primary_nuance\": \"The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]he is none of his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is an older possessive idiom meaning \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]does not belong to him,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] while the Greek \[Omicron]\:1f57\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f14\[Sigma]\[Tau]\[Iota]\[Nu] \[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 states non-belonging to Christ rather than a vague loss of identity.\",\n  \"category\": \"archaic-english-drift\",\n  \"key_term\": \"\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f30\[Mu]\:03af\",\n  \"english_drift\": \"\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]none of his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] = in early modern English, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]not one belonging to him / not his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; in modern English it can sound opaque or merely idiomatic rather than explicitly possessive.\",\n  \"textual_note\": \"\",\n  \"cross_refs\": [\n    \"1 Cor 3:16\",\n    \"Gal 4:6\",\n    \"Rom 8:14\"\n  ],\n  \"explanation\": \"There is no meaningful TR/SBLGNT divergence here; the issue is chiefly idiom and aspect. \[Omicron]\:1f57\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Kappa] \:1f14\[Sigma]\[Tau]\[Iota]\[Nu] \[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1fe6 is a genitive of possession or relationship: \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]this one is not his,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] i.e. does not belong to Christ. The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]he is none of his\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] was intelligible early modern English, but now risks opacity; the modern rendering makes the possessive force explicit. Likewise \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]if so be that\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] renders \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f34\[Pi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Rho], which BDAG treats as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]if indeed / if in fact\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; with the indicative \[Omicron]\:1f30\[Kappa]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fd6 it is not a subjunctive \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]might dwell,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] but a condition assumed for Paul\[CloseCurlyQuote]s addressees. The KJV\[CloseCurlyQuote]s bare \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]dwell\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] also reflects older English verbal usage, whereas \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]dwells\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] marks the present indicative more transparently. The alternation \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Spirit of God\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] / \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Spirit of Christ\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is in the Greek and is theologically significant, but not a KJV addition.\"\n}"|>, <|"ref" -> "Ro 8:38", "greek" -> "\[Pi]\:03ad\[Pi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Iota]\[Sigma]\[Mu]\[Alpha]\[Iota] \[Gamma]\:1f70\[Rho] \:1f45\[Tau]\[Iota] \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Theta]\:03ac\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Zeta]\[Omega]\:1f74 \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \:1f04\[Gamma]\[Gamma]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Lambda]\[Omicron]\[Iota] \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \:1f00\[Rho]\[Chi]\[Alpha]\:1f76 \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \:1f10\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:1ff6\[Tau]\[Alpha] \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Mu]\:03ad\[Lambda]\[Lambda]\[Omicron]\[Nu]\[Tau]\[Alpha] \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Delta]\[Upsilon]\[Nu]\:03ac\[Mu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Iota]\[FinalSigma]", "kjv" -> "For I am persuaded, that neither death, nor life, nor angels, nor principalities, nor powers, nor things present, nor things to come,", "modern" -> "For I am convinced that neither death nor life nor angels nor rulers nor things present nor things to come nor powers", "distance" -> 0.14487255313887937, "nuance" -> <|"primary_nuance" -> "The KJV follows the Textus Receptus/Byzantine order by placing \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]powers\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] immediately after \[OpenCu