  "iliad3way" -> {<|"ref" -> "Il. 1.1-7 (the proem)", "greek" -> "\[Mu]\:1fc6\[Nu]\[Iota]\[Nu] \:1f04\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Iota]\[Delta]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Theta]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f70 \[CapitalPi]\[Eta]\[Lambda]\[Eta]\:03ca\:03ac\[Delta]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Omega] \:1f08\[Chi]\[Iota]\[Lambda]\:1fc6\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Lambda]\[Omicron]\[Mu]\:03ad\[Nu]\[Eta]\[Nu], \:1f23 \[Mu]\[Upsilon]\[Rho]\:03af\:1fbd \:1f08\[Chi]\[Alpha]\[Iota]\[Omicron]\:1fd6\[FinalSigma] \:1f04\[Lambda]\[Gamma]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fbd \:1f14\[Theta]\[Eta]\[Kappa]\[CurlyEpsilon], \[Pi]\[Omicron]\[Lambda]\[Lambda]\:1f70\[FinalSigma] \[Delta]\:1fbd \:1f30\[CurlyPhi]\[Theta]\:03af\[Mu]\[Omicron]\[Upsilon]\[FinalSigma] \[Psi]\[Upsilon]\[Chi]\:1f70\[FinalSigma] \:1f0c\:03ca\[Delta]\[Iota] \[Pi]\[Rho]\[Omicron]\:0390\[Alpha]\[Psi]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Nu] \:1f21\[Rho]\:03ce\[Omega]\[Nu], \[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:1f7a\[FinalSigma] \[Delta]\:1f72 \:1f11\[Lambda]\:03ce\[Rho]\[Iota]\[Alpha] \[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fe6\[Chi]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Kappa]\:03cd\[Nu]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Sigma]\[Sigma]\[Iota]\[Nu] \[Omicron]\:1f30\[Omega]\[Nu]\[Omicron]\:1fd6\[Sigma]\:03af \[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Pi]\:1fb6\[Sigma]\[Iota], \[CapitalDelta]\[Iota]\:1f78\[FinalSigma] \[Delta]\:1fbd \:1f10\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Lambda]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:03af\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Tau]\[Omicron] \[Beta]\[Omicron]\[Upsilon]\[Lambda]\:03ae, \:1f10\[Xi] \[Omicron]\:1f57 \[Delta]\:1f74 \[Tau]\:1f70 \[Pi]\[Rho]\:1ff6\[Tau]\[Alpha] \[Delta]\[Iota]\[Alpha]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:03ae\[Tau]\[Eta]\[Nu] \:1f10\[Rho]\:03af\[Sigma]\[Alpha]\[Nu]\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \:1f08\[Tau]\[Rho]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:0390\[Delta]\[Eta]\[FinalSigma] \[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \:1f04\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Xi] \:1f00\[Nu]\[Delta]\[Rho]\:1ff6\[Nu] \[Kappa]\[Alpha]\:1f76 \[Delta]\:1fd6\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \:1f08\[Chi]\[Iota]\[Lambda]\[Lambda]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:03cd\[FinalSigma].", "pope" -> "Achilles' wrath, to Greece the direful spring Of woes unnumber'd, heavenly goddess, sing! That wrath which hurl'd to Pluto's gloomy reign The souls of mighty chiefs untimely slain; Whose limbs unburied on the naked shore, Devouring dogs and hungry vultures tore. Since great Achilles and Atrides strove, Such was the sovereign doom, and such the will of Jove!", "butler" -> "Sing, O goddess, the anger of Achilles son of Peleus, that brought countless ills upon the Achaeans. Many a brave soul did it send hurrying down to Hades, and many a hero did it yield a prey to dogs and vultures, for so were the counsels of Jove fulfilled from the day on which the son of Atreus, king of men, and great Achilles, first fell out with one another.", "modern" -> "Sing, goddess, the ruinous wrath of Achilles son of Peleus,\nwhich laid countless pains upon the Achaeans,\nand sent forth to Hades many strong souls of heroes,\nand made them themselves spoil for dogs\nand for all birds; and the plan of Zeus was being brought to fulfillment,\nfrom the time when first they two stood apart in strife,\nthe son of Atreus, lord of men, and brilliant Achilles.", "labels" -> {"greek", "pope", "butler", "modern"}, "nuance" -> <|"headline" -> "Pope turns Homer\[CloseCurlyQuote]s compressed causal proem into a neoclassical tableau, Butler paraphrases it into fluent prose, while the modern version tries to preserve the Greek\[CloseCurlyQuote]s formulaic pressure and syntax.", "pope_signature" -> "Pope\[CloseCurlyQuote]s characteristic move is expansion: he retains the agency of wrath but ornaments it with causal metaphor, affective adjectives, and Latinate mythological diction. Phrases such as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]direful spring,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]gloomy reign,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]naked shore,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]sovereign doom\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] are not in the Greek.", "butler_signature" -> "Butler is semantically closer than Pope, but his prose often domesticates epic formula into plain narrative. His \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]anger,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]fell out,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]great Achilles\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] flatten the marked diction of \[Mu]\:1fc6\[Nu]\[Iota]\[Nu], \[Delta]\[Iota]\[Alpha]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:03ae\[Tau]\[Eta]\[Nu] \:1f10\[Rho]\:03af\[Sigma]\[Alpha]\[Nu]\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon], and \[Delta]\:1fd6\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \:1f08\[Chi]\[Iota]\[Lambda]\[Lambda]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:03cd\[FinalSigma].", "greek_lemma" -> "\[Omicron]\:1f50\[Lambda]\[Omicron]\[Mu]\:03ad\[Nu]\[Eta]\[Nu]", "explanation" -> "The pivotal Greek is \[Mu]\:1fc6\[Nu]\[Iota]\[Nu], immediately qualified by \[Omicron]\:1f50\[Lambda]\[Omicron]\[Mu]\:03ad\[Nu]\[Eta]\[Nu]: not generic anger but a destructive wrath with epic agency. Modern keeps this compactly (\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]ruinous wrath\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) and Butler reduces it to \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]anger,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] omitting the participial epithet; Pope keeps \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]wrath\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] but amplifies it into \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]the direful spring / Of woes unnumber\[CloseCurlyQuote]d,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] a causal metaphor not in \:1f23 \[Mu]\[Upsilon]\[Rho]\:03af\:1fbd ... \:1f04\[Lambda]\[Gamma]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:1fbd \:1f14\[Theta]\[Eta]\[Kappa]\[CurlyEpsilon] (\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]which laid countless pains\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]). Pope\[CloseCurlyQuote]s neoclassical hand is still more visible in \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Pluto\[CloseCurlyQuote]s gloomy reign,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]untimely slain,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]naked shore,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]hungry vultures,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]sovereign doom\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]: none corresponds to \:1f0c\:03ca\[Delta]\[Iota], \:1f11\[Lambda]\:03ce\[Rho]\[Iota]\[Alpha], \[Omicron]\:1f30\[Omega]\[Nu]\[Omicron]\:1fd6\[Sigma]\:03af \[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Pi]\:1fb6\[Sigma]\[Iota], or \[CapitalDelta]\[Iota]\:1f78\[FinalSigma] ... \[Beta]\[Omicron]\[Upsilon]\[Lambda]\:03ae, though they ornament and moralize the scene. Butler\[CloseCurlyQuote]s prose is generally semantically conservative, but it flattens formulaic texture: \[Delta]\:1fd6\[Omicron]\[FinalSigma] \:1f08\[Chi]\[Iota]\[Lambda]\[Lambda]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:03cd\[FinalSigma] becomes \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]great Achilles\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; \:1f08\[Tau]\[Rho]\[CurlyEpsilon]\:0390\[Delta]\[Eta]\[FinalSigma] \[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \:1f04\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Xi] \:1f00\[Nu]\[Delta]\[Rho]\:1ff6\[Nu] is translated rather than allowed as a resonant epithet; \[Delta]\[Iota]\[Alpha]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:03ae\[Tau]\[Eta]\[Nu] \:1f10\[Rho]\:03af\[Sigma]\[Alpha]\[Nu]\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] becomes colloquial \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]fell out,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] losing the physicalized \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]stood apart in strife.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] He also blurs the sharp \[Psi]\[Upsilon]\[Chi]\:03ac\[FinalSigma]/\[Alpha]\:1f50\[Tau]\[Omicron]\:03cd\[FinalSigma] contrast by \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]many a brave soul ... many a hero,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] whereas the Modern renders the bodies as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]them themselves spoil.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] The cosine distances corroborate this reading at a coarse level: Butler\[Dash]Modern is closest (0.139), while Pope is farther from both. They also reveal only surface/semantic affinity, not philological fidelity: Pope\[Dash]Modern\[CloseCurlyQuote]s slight closeness over Pope\[Dash]Butler likely reflects shared \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]wrath\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and high-register diction, but the numbers cannot detect Pope\[CloseCurlyQuote]s added \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]gloomy,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]hungry,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] or \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]sovereign doom,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] nor Butler\[CloseCurlyQuote]s loss of \[Pi]\:1fb6\[Sigma]\[Iota] (\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]all\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote])."|>, "dmat" -> {{0., 0.8315990537714512, 0.8061625992519191, 0.8094722483820549}, {0.8315990537714512, 0., 0.19959074054198855, 0.19144580178366466}, {0.8061625992519191, 0.19959074054198855, 0., 0.13895157685502868}, {0.8094722483820549, 0.19144580178366466, 0.13895157685502868, 0.}}|>, <|"ref" -> "Il. 1.225-228 (Achilles to Agamemnon)", "greek" -> "\[Omicron]\:1f30\[Nu]\[Omicron]\[Beta]\[Alpha]\[Rho]\:03ad\[FinalSigma], \[Kappa]\[Upsilon]\[Nu]\:1f78\[FinalSigma] \:1f44\[Mu]\[Mu]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\:1fbd \:1f14\[Chi]\[Omega]\[Nu], \[Kappa]\[Rho]\[Alpha]\[Delta]\:03af\[Eta]\[Nu] \[Delta]\:1fbd \:1f10\[Lambda]\:03ac\[CurlyPhi]\[Omicron]\[Iota]\[Omicron], \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Pi]\[Omicron]\[Tau]\:1fbd \:1f10\[FinalSigma] \[Pi]\:03cc\[Lambda]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Mu]\[Omicron]\[Nu] \:1f05\[Mu]\[Alpha] \[Lambda]\[Alpha]\:1ff7 \[Theta]\[Omega]\[Rho]\[Eta]\[Chi]\[Theta]\:1fc6\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Iota] \[Omicron]\:1f54\[Tau]\[CurlyEpsilon] \[Lambda]\:03cc\[Chi]\[Omicron]\[Nu]\[Delta]\:1fbd \:1f30\:03ad\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Iota] \[Sigma]\:1f7a\[Nu] \:1f00\[Rho]\[Iota]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:03ae\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Sigma]\[Sigma]\[Iota]\[Nu] \:1f08\[Chi]\[Alpha]\[Iota]\:1ff6\[Nu] \[Tau]\:03ad\[Tau]\[Lambda]\[Eta]\[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[FinalSigma] \[Theta]\[Upsilon]\[Mu]\:1ff7\[CenterDot] \[Tau]\:1f78 \[Delta]\:03ad \[Tau]\[Omicron]\[Iota] \[Kappa]\:1f74\[Rho] \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f34\[Delta]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Tau]\[Alpha]\[Iota] \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f36\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Iota].", "pope" -> "O monster, mix'd of insolence and fear, Thou dog in forehead, but in heart a deer! When wert thou known in ambush'd fights to dare, Or nobly face the horrid front of war? 'Tis ours, the chance of fighting fields to try; Thine to look on, and bid the valiant die.", "butler" -> "Wine-bibber, with the face of a dog and the heart of a hind, you never dare to go out with the host in fight, nor yet with our chosen men in ambuscade. You shun this as you do death itself.", "modern" -> "Wine-soaked, with the eyes of a dog and the heart of a deer, you have never yet dared in your spirit either to arm yourself for battle with the host or to go into ambush with the best of the Achaeans; that, to your heart, seems to be death.", "labels" -> {"greek", "pope", "butler", "modern"}, "nuance" -> <|"headline" -> "Pope converts Homer\[CloseCurlyQuote]s compact abuse into Augustan moral spectacle, while Butler stays denotatively close but smooths away formulaic and imagistic sharpness.", "pope_signature" -> "Pope\[CloseCurlyQuote]s characteristic move is amplification: he personifies and moralizes what Homer leaves as brutal epithets and infinitives. His couplet logic adds antitheses and judgments absent from the Greek.", "butler_signature" -> "Butler\[CloseCurlyQuote]s prose tracks the sense more closely, but it domesticates Homeric diction. He often translates formulaic or embodied language into serviceable English idiom.", "greek_lemma" -> "\[Kappa]\:1f74\[Rho]", "explanation" -> "The Greek insult is paratactic and formulaic: \[Omicron]\:1f30\[Nu]\[Omicron]\[Beta]\[Alpha]\[Rho]\:03ad\[FinalSigma], \[Kappa]\[Upsilon]\[Nu]\:1f78\[FinalSigma] \:1f44\[Mu]\[Mu]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\:1fbd \:1f14\[Chi]\[Omega]\[Nu], \[Kappa]\[Rho]\[Alpha]\[Delta]\:03af\[Eta]\[Nu] \[Delta]\:1fbd \:1f10\[Lambda]\:03ac\[CurlyPhi]\[Omicron]\[Iota]\[Omicron] gives three blows, then two infinitival tests governed by \[Tau]\:03ad\[Tau]\[Lambda]\[Eta]\[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[FinalSigma] \[Theta]\[Upsilon]\[Mu]\:1ff7. Pope turns this into moral theatre. \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]O monster, mix\[CloseCurlyQuote]d of insolence and fear\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] has no lexical counterpart; neither do \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]nobly,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]the horrid front of war,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] or the closing antithesis \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]\[CloseCurlyQuote]Tis ours...Thine...\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] He recasts Achilles\[CloseCurlyQuote] taunt as a neoclassical indictment of command, expanding \[Tau]\:1f78 \[Delta]\:03ad \[Tau]\[Omicron]\[Iota] \[Kappa]\:1f74\[Rho] \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f34\[Delta]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Tau]\[Alpha]\[Iota] \[CurlyEpsilon]\:1f36\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Iota] into Agamemnon\[CloseCurlyQuote]s habit of watching and making others die. Butler is much closer in reference, but his prose often de-formularizes. \[Kappa]\[Upsilon]\[Nu]\:1f78\[FinalSigma] \:1f44\[Mu]\[Mu]\[Alpha]\[Tau]\:1fbd becomes \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]the face of a dog,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] losing the pointed \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]eyes\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; \:1f10\[FinalSigma] \[Pi]\:03cc\[Lambda]\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Mu]\[Omicron]\[Nu] \:1f05\[Mu]\[Alpha] \[Lambda]\[Alpha]\:1ff7 \[Theta]\[Omega]\[Rho]\[Eta]\[Chi]\[Theta]\:1fc6\[Nu]\[Alpha]\[Iota], literally \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]to arm yourself for war with the people/host,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] becomes the generic \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]go out with the host in fight\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]; \:1f00\[Rho]\[Iota]\[Sigma]\[Tau]\:03ae\[CurlyEpsilon]\[Sigma]\[Sigma]\[Iota]\[Nu] \:1f08\[Chi]\[Alpha]\[Iota]\:1ff6\[Nu] becomes \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]our chosen men,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] not \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]the best of the Achaeans.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] Most consequentially, \[Tau]\:03ad\[Tau]\[Lambda]\[Eta]\[Kappa]\[Alpha]\[FinalSigma] \[Theta]\[Upsilon]\[Mu]\:1ff7 and \[Kappa]\:1f74\[Rho] are flattened into idiom: \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]You shun this as you do death itself,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] whereas Homer says it \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]seems to you to be death/doom,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] locating cowardice in perception and \[Theta]\[Upsilon]\[Mu]\:03cc\[FinalSigma]. The distances corroborate, rather than explain, this: Butler\[Dash]Modern (.244) is lowest because both preserve the line\[CloseCurlyQuote]s denotative scaffold; Pope is farther (.343/.384) because of couplet amplification. They also reveal that vector proximity can miss philological texture: Butler\[CloseCurlyQuote]s close score coexists with losses in formula, anatomy, and heroic register."|>, "dmat" -> {{0., 0.9304878349794252, 0.9262163502150509, 0.8427078597805254}, {0.9304878349794252, 0., 0.3432336230321327, 0.3840206415753433}, {0.9262163502150509, 0.3432336230321327, 0., 0.2436245512624604}, {0.8427078597805254, 0.3840206415753433, 0.2436245512624604, 0.}}|>},
  "tao2way" -> {<|"ch" -> 1, "chinese" -> "\:9053\:53ef\:9053\:ff0c\:975e\:5e38\:9053\:3002\:540d\:53ef\:540d\:ff0c\:975e\:5e38\:540d\:3002\:7121\:ff0c\:540d\:5929\:5730\:4e4b\:59cb\:fe54\:6709\:ff0c\:540d\:842c\:7269\:4e4b\:6bcd\:3002\:6545\:5e38\:7121\:ff0c\:6b32\:4ee5\:89c0\:5176\:5999\:ff1b\:5e38\:6709\:ff0c\:6b32\:4ee5\:89c0\:5176\:5fbc\:3002\:6b64\:5169\:8005\:ff0c\:540c\:51fa\:800c\:7570\:540d\:ff0c\:540c\:8b02\:4e4b\:7384\:3002\:7384\:4e4b\:53c8\:7384\:ff0c\:773e\:5999\:4e4b\:9580\:3002", "legge" -> "The Tao that can be trodden is not the enduring and unchanging Tao. The name that can be named is not the enduring and unchanging name. (Conceived of as) having no name, it is the Originator of heaven and earth; (conceived of as) having a name, it is the Mother of all things. Always without desire we must be found, If its deep mystery we would sound; But if desire always within us be, Its outer fringe is all that we shall see. Under these two aspects, it is really the same; but as development takes place, it receives the different names. Together we call them the Mystery. Where the Mystery is the deepest is the gate of all that is subtle and wonderful.", "modern" -> "The Dao that can be spoken is not the constant Dao.\nThe name that can be named is not the constant name.\nNon-being is named as the beginning of heaven and earth;\nbeing is named as the mother of the ten thousand things.\nThus, constant non-being: desire thereby to observe its subtlety;\nconstant being: desire thereby to observe its boundary.\nThese two emerge together but differ in name;\ntogether they are called darkly profound.\nDarkly profound and again darkly profound:\nthe gate of the many subtleties.", "d_zh_legge" -> 0.6722840463674644, "d_zh_modern" -> 0.6598863383911442, "d_legge_modern" -> 0.18812314243146977, "nuance" -> <|"headline" -> "Legge turns the chapter\[CloseCurlyQuote]s ontological pair \:7121/\:6709 into two \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]aspects\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] of a named or nameless divine source, while the modern rendering keeps the starker grammar of non-being/being.", "abstract_noun" -> "\:7121/\:6709 (w\[UAcute]/y\:01d2u), \:7384 (xu\[AAcute]n)", "victorian_marker" -> "Explanatory parentheticals, periphrastic \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]enduring and unchanging,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and rhymed moralizing verse", "christianising" -> "\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Originator\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and capitalized \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Mystery\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]", "explanation" -> "The sharpest divergence is at \:7121\:ff0c\:540d\:5929\:5730\:4e4b\:59cb\:ff1b\:6709\:ff0c\:540d\:842c\:7269\:4e4b\:6bcd. Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote](Conceived of as) having no name\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] effectively reads \:7121\:540d and \:6709\:540d, making the issue namelessness versus nameability. The modern version instead treats \:7121 and \:6709 as abstract ontological terms: \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Non-being is named\[Ellipsis]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]being is named\[Ellipsis]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]. That is closer to the Wang Bi punctuation as supplied, where \:7121 and \:6709 stand before the comma. Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Originator of heaven and earth\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] also goes beyond \:59cb, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]beginning,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] importing a quasi-creator term; \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Mother\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is in the Chinese \:6bcd, but \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Originator\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is not.\n\nAt \:9053\:53ef\:9053, Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]can be trodden\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] foregrounds \:9053 as a path, whereas \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]can be spoken\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] makes \:9053 verbal and pairs it with \:540d\:53ef\:540d, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]the name that can be named.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] His \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]enduring and unchanging\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is a Victorian expansion of \:5e38; \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]constant\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is plainer and less metaphysical.\n\nThe desire lines also differ grammatically. Legge reads \:5e38\:7121\:6b32 / \:5e38\:6709\:6b32: \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Always without desire\[Ellipsis]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] versus \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]if desire\[Ellipsis]\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] The modern parses \:5e38\:7121 and \:5e38\:6709, taking \:6b32 as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]desire/wish thereby to observe,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] so the objects of contemplation are \:7121 and \:6709 themselves, not the sage\[CloseCurlyQuote]s psychology. Finally, Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s capitalized \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Mystery\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] for \:7384 theologicalizes what literally suggests the dark, obscure, profound; \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]darkly profound\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] preserves that semantic color."|>|>, <|"ch" -> 2, "chinese" -> "\:5929\:4e0b\:7686\:77e5\:7f8e\:4e4b\:70ba\:7f8e\:ff0c\:65af\:60e1\:77e3\:fe54\:7686\:77e5\:5584\:4e4b\:70ba\:5584\:ff0c\:65af\:4e0d\:5584\:77e3\:3002\:6545\:6709\:7121\:76f8\:751f\:ff0c\:96e3\:6613\:76f8\:6210\:ff0c\:9577\:77ed\:76f8\:5f62\:ff0c\:9ad8\:4e0b\:76f8\:50be\:ff0c\:97f3\:8072\:76f8\:548c\:ff0c\:524d\:5f8c\:76f8\:96a8\:3002\:662f\:4ee5\:8056\:4eba\:8655\:300c\:7121\:70ba\:300d\:4e4b\:4e8b\:ff0c\:884c\:300c\:4e0d\:8a00\:300d\:4e4b\:6559\:3002\:842c\:7269\:4f5c\:7109\:800c\:4e0d\:8fad\:ff0c\:751f\:800c\:4e0d\:6709\:ff0c\:70ba\:800c\:4e0d\:6043\:ff0c\:529f\:6210\:800c\:5f17\:5c45\:3002\:592b\:552f\:5f17\:5c45\:ff0c\:662f\:4ee5\:4e0d\:53bb\:3002", "legge" -> "All in the world know the beauty of the beautiful, and in doing this they have (the idea of) what ugliness is; they all know the skill of the skilful, and in doing this they have (the idea of) what the want of skill is. So it is that existence and non-existence give birth the one to (the idea of) the other; that difficulty and ease produce the one (the idea of) the other; that length and shortness fashion out the one the figure of the other; that (the ideas of) height and lowness arise from the contrast of the one with the other; that the musical notes and tones become harmonious through the relation of one with another; and that being before and behind give the idea of one following another. Therefore the sage manages affairs without doing anything, and conveys his instructions without the use of speech.", "modern" -> "When all under Heaven know the beautiful as beautiful, then the ugly is already present;\nwhen all know the good as good, then the not-good is already present.\nTherefore being and non-being give rise to one another;\ndifficult and easy complete one another;\nlong and short give form to one another;\nhigh and low incline toward one another;\ntone and sound harmonize with one another;\nbefore and after follow one another.\nFor this reason, the sage dwells in the work of without-action\nand carries out the teaching without words.\nThe ten thousand things arise there, yet are not refused;\ngenerated, yet not possessed;\nacted, yet not relied upon;\nthe work accomplished, yet not dwelt in.\nPrecisely because it is not dwelt in,\ntherefore it does not depart.", "d_zh_legge" -> 0.6249291058727536, "d_zh_modern" -> 0.6188862600920441, "d_legge_modern" -> 0.21372016866463628, "nuance" -> <|"headline" -> "Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s decisive nuance is to psychologize Laozi\[CloseCurlyQuote]s reciprocal opposites as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]ideas,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] while the modern rendering keeps them as co-arising relations.", "abstract_noun" -> "\:6709/\:7121 (y\:01d2u/w\[UAcute]); \:7121\:70ba (w\[UAcute]w\[EAcute]i)", "victorian_marker" -> "Repeated parenthetical glosses such as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote](the idea of)\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and explanatory abstract diction", "christianising" -> "", "explanation" -> "Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s most consequential move is to make Laozi\[CloseCurlyQuote]s correlations psychological. Where \:5929\:4e0b\:7686\:77e5\:7f8e\:4e4b\:70ba\:7f8e\:ff0c\:65af\:60e1\:77e3 says that once \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]beauty\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is recognized as beauty, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]ugliness\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] (\:60e1) is thereby in play, Legge writes that people have \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote](the idea of) what ugliness is.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] His recurring parenthetical \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote](the idea of)\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] before ugliness, the other, height/lowness, and before/behind turns \:76f8\:751f/\:76f8\:6210 etc. into the generation of concepts. The modern \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]already present\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]give rise/complete/give form ... to one another\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] keeps the Chinese reciprocal \:76f8 as relational co-constitution, not merely mental contrast. Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \:5584 as \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]the skill of the skilful\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is also notable: \:5584 can mean adept, but paired with \:7f8e and opposed to \:4e0d\:5584 it more naturally reads \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]good,\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] so his wording de-moralizes the line into competence. For \:6709\:7121, Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]existence and non-existence\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is Victorian metaphysical diction; \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]being and non-being\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] is equally abstract but less explanatory and closer to later Daoist terminology. At \:7121\:70ba, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]without doing anything\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] risks simple passivity, whereas \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]without-action\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] flags a technical term for non-coercive action. Likewise Legge\[CloseCurlyQuote]s \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]manages affairs\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] and \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]conveys his instructions\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] make \:8655...\:4e8b and \:884c...\:6559 sound administrative and pedagogic. As quoted, Legge also stops before \:842c\:7269\:4f5c\:7109...\:5f17\:5c45, so the modern\[CloseCurlyQuote]s anti-possession refrain has no Legge counterpart here. No specifically Christian vocabulary appears in this chapter."|>|>},
